Claims CLAIMS What is claimed is: 1. A stackable wear panel (1 ) for use within a modular stackable wearresistant panel system (11 ), the stackable wear panel (1 ) being configured to be removably affixed to a wall (10A) or surface of equipment (10) to be protected - and also configured to be alternatively removably affixed to a top surface (2A) of another stackable wear panel (1 ) within a stacked wear panel arrangement (1 the stackable wear panel (1 ) comprising: a matrix (2) having a top surface (2A), a bottom surface (2B) opposite said top surface (2), and a central bore (4) extending through the top (2A) and bottom (2B) surfaces and receiving a fastener (5) or a spacing adapter (6) therein, the central bore (4) being configured to support a portion (5A, 5B) of the fastener (5) or a lower outer surface portion (6E) of the spacing adapter (6). 2. The stackable wear panel (1 ) according to claim 1 , wherein the fastener (5) is a bolt (5) comprising a head (5A), and the central bore (4) is configured to support a lower head surface (5B) provided beneath the head (5A). 3. The stackable wear panel (1 ) according to any one of the preceding claims, wherein the lower outer surface portion (6E) of the spacing adapter (6) comprises a tapered surface, a rounded surface, or a chamfer which is configured to bias the spacing adapter (6) into coaxial alignment with the central bore (4). 4. The stackable wear panel (1 ) according to any one of the preceding claims, wherein the stackable wear panel (1 ) is part of a stacked wear panel arrangement (1 ', 1") comprising a first matrix (2) and a second matrix (2), the first matrix (2) being configured to be removably affixed to the wall (10A) or surface of equipment (10) to be protected, and comprising a first central bore (4) having a spacing adapter (6) disposed therein, a bottom surface (2B) of the second matrix (2) being positioned against a top surface (2A) of the first matrix (2), the second matrix (2) comprising a second central bore (4) having a head (5A) of the fastener (5) therein. 5. The stackable wear panel (1 ) according to any one of the preceding claims, wherein the spacing adapter (6) comprises an aperture (6b) comprising an inner thread (6C), the inner thread (6C) being configured for threaded engagement with an outer threaded shaft (6C) of the fastener (5). 6. The stackable wear panel (1 ) according to any one of the preceding claims, wherein the fastener (5) is configured for threaded engagement with a nut (5E) provided to a back side of the wall (10A) or surface. 7. The stackable wear panel (1 ) according to any one of the preceding claims, wherein the matrix (2) comprises a number of cavities (3, 7). 8. The stackable wear panel (1 ) according to claim 7, wherein the number of cavities (3, 7) comprises a number of through-cavities (3) extending through the top surface (2A) and the bottom surface (2B) of the matrix (2). 9. The stackable wear panel (1 ) according to claim 7 or 8, wherein the number of cavities (3, 7) comprises a number of blind-cavities (7, 7A, 7B) extending into the top surface (2A) of the matrix and/or bottom surface (2B) of the matrix (2). 10. The stackable wear panel (1 ) according to any one of claims 7-9, wherein the number of cavities (3, 7) comprises a taper (3A, 3B). 11. The stackable wear panel (1 ) according to any one of claims 7-10, wherein the number of cavities (3, 7, 7A, 7B) comprise or are filled with a polymer. 12. The stackable wear panel (1 ) according to claims 11 , wherein the polymer comprises urethane or hard rubber. 13. A method of installing a stackable wear panel (1 ) onto a wall (10A) or surface of a piece of equipment (10), the stackable wear panel (1 ) being part of a modular stackable wear-resistant panel system (1 1 ), the method comprising the steps of: providing a matrix (2) according to any one of the preceding claims; 

 inserting the fastener (5) through the central bore (4) of the matrix (2); supporting the fastener (5) within the central bore (4) such that the portion of the fastener (5) engages a surface portion of the central bore (4); preventing further passage of the fastener (5) beyond the lower surface (2B) of the matrix (2) using the central bore (4); applying a nut (5E) to an outer threaded shaft (5C) of the fastener (5); and, securing the matrix (2) against relative movement with respect to the wall (10A) or surface of a piece of equipment (10) by virtue of tightening the nut (5E) in relation to the outer threaded shaft (5C) of the fastener (5). 14. The method according to 13, further comprising: providing a second identical matrix (2) according to any one of the preceding claims; arranging said second identical matrix (2) below said matrix (2) described in claim 13, such that the bottom surface (2B) of said matrix (2) described in claim 13 is in close proximity with the top surface (2A) of the second identical matrix (2); providing the spacing adapter (6) within the central bore (4) of the second identical matrix (2), the spacing adapter (6) having an aperture (6B) outfitted with an inner thread (6C); and; engaging the inner thread (6C) with the outer threaded shaft (5C) of the fastener (5) prior to the step of applying a nut (5E) to an outer threaded shaft (5C) of the fastener (5). 15. The method according to 14, further comprising: providing a third identical matrix (2) according to any one of the preceding claims; arranging said third identical matrix (2) below or above said second identical matrix (2) described in claim 14 such that the bottom surface (2B) of said second identical matrix (2) described in claim 14 is in close proximity with the top surface (2A) of the third identical matrix (2) - or, such that the bottom surface (2B) of said third identical matrix (2) is in close proximity with the top surface (2A) of the second identical matrix (2) described in claim 14; 

 providing another spacing adapter (6) identical to the spacing adapter (6) of claim 14 within the central bore (4) of the third identical matrix (2); and; engaging the inner thread (6C) of said another spacing adapter (6) with the outer threaded shaft (5C) of the fastener (5) prior to the step of applying a nut (5E) to an outer threaded shaft (5C) of the fastener (5). 16. A modular stackable wear-resistant panel system (11 ) comprising: a plurality of the matrix (2) defined in any one of the preceding claims; a plurality of the spacing adapter (6) defined in any one of the preceding claims; and a plurality of the fastener (5) defined in any one of the preceding claims; wherein the modular stackable wear-resistant panel system (1 1 ) is configured such that: a single one of said plurality of matrix (2) may be secured to the wall (10A) or surface of a piece of equipment (10) via a single one of said plurality of fastener (5); two of said plurality of matrix (2) may be secured to the wall (10A) or surface of a piece of equipment (10) via said single one of said plurality of fastener (5) and a single one of said plurality of spacing adapter (6); and three of said plurality of matrix (2) may be secured to the wall (10A) or surface of a piece of equipment (10) via said single one of said plurality of fastener (5) and two of said plurality of spacing adapter (6).
